&lt;p&gt;Neurological Rehabilitation Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxford Centre for Enablement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 7 Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time 18.75 hours per week- Wednesday afternoon , Thursday and Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic Occupational Therapist with neurological rehabilitation experience to join our enthusiastic, innovative and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will job share with another band 7 Occupational Therapist. They will work within our interdisciplinary team (IDT) providing specialist Occupational Therapy assessment and treatment to inpatients, who have a variety of complex neurological conditions, at our level 1 Regional Rehabilitation Unit. The post holder also provides Occupational Therapy leadership to the other Occupational Therapists (OTs) working with inpatients. They are responsible for organising and managing their own caseload and overseeing the caseload allocation of the other inpatient OTs. Direct supervision of band 6 staff and Occupational Therapy students is an integral part of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The involvement in evidenced based projects/audit to further enhance the team’s clinical practice is actively encouraged, and taking a lead in IDT service development projects is a key role . The post holder will also be involved in presenting on external courses, the unit runs, for national delegates and delivering training to the OT and IDT teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills, an ability to prioritise workload effectively and work as part of an interdisciplinary team are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oxford Centre for Enablement houses a number of specialist neurological services with excellent opportunities for informal and formal continuing professional development. Quality improvement projects are actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit. please contact Alison Bragg Lead OT on 01865 737380&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planned Interview Date: 24th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
